article.description: Brian Green came off the bench to score a career-high 25 points and Utah State extended its winning streak to 14 games with an 84-65 win over San Jose State on Thursday night.
article.headline: Brian Green comes off bench to give No. 25 Utah State boost
article.linkText: Green scores 25 off bench to lift No. 25 Utah St.
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Brian Green came off the bench to score a career-high 25 points and Utah State (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) extended its winning streak to 14 games with an 84-65 win over San Jose State on Thursday night. Green made his first eight shots from the floor, including five 3-pointers, and didn't miss until six minutes remained in the game. Green also matched his career-best of six rebounds. Pooh Williams added 14 points, and Brockeith Pane and Brady Jardine each scored 13 points for Utah State (19-2, 8-0 WAC). The Aggies also extended their conference-record winning streak to 22 games. Adrian Oliver had 29 points for San Jose State (9-10, 1-7).
